SIMPLE: prevent
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prevent
<hw>Pre*vent"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Prevented</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Preventing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>praevenire</ets>,
<ets>praeventum</ets>; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>venire</ets> to
come. See <er>Come</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To go before; to
precede; hence, to go before as a guide; to direct.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We which are alive and remain unto the coming of the Lord shall
not <qex>prevent</qex> them which are asleep.</q> <rj><qau>1 Thess. iv.
15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We pray thee that thy grace may always <qex>prevent</qex> and
follow us.</q> <rj><qau>Bk. of Common Prayer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then had I come, <qex>preventing</qex> Sheba's queen.</q>
<rj><qau>Prior.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be beforehand with; to anticipate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their ready guilt <qex>preventing</qex> thy commands.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To intercept; to hinder; to frustrate; to stop; to
thwart.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧This vile purpose to <xex>prevent</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Perhaps forestalling night <qex>prevented</qex> them.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prevent</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prevent
<hw>Pre*vent"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To come before the usual
time.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Strawberries . . . will <qex>prevent</qex> and come early.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preventability</ent>⟦br⟧
